column1: German ELV transactions can be processed with an integrated credit and address check. The merchant has to agree with CreditPass (Telego) the test rules. The test rule is referred to by a 'Purchase Type'. If you don't want to use this feature, you can leave this field empty.
column2: Transacciones alemanas ELV se pueden procesar con un crédito integrado y verificación de la dirección. El comerciante tiene que estar de acuerdo con (Telego) reglas de prueba CreditPass. Mediante la definición del 'Purchase Type' se puede especificar la regla de prueba. Si no desea utilizar esta función, puede dejar este campo vacío.

column1: Here you can define a Shop ID. This is only necessary if you wish to operate several shops with one Datatrans account. In order to use this module, an additional module is required.

column1: Here you can insert a transaction prefix. The prefix allows you to change the transaction number that is transmitted to Datatrans. The prefix must contain the tag {id}. It will then be replaced by the order number (e.g. name_{id}).
column2: El prefijo le permite cambiar el número de transacciones que se transmite a Datatrans. El prefijo debe contener la etiqueta {id}. A continuación, se sustituye por el número de orden (por ejemplo name_ {id}).

column1: Here you can insert an order prefix. The prefix allows you to change the order number that is transmitted to Authorize.net. The prefix must contain the tag {id}. It will then be replaced by the order number (e.g. name_{id}).
column2: Here you can insert an order prefix. The prefix allows you to change the order number that is transmitted to Authorize.net. The prefix must contain the tag {id}. It will then be replaced by the order number (e.g. name_{id}).

column1: Here you can set if the invoice will be sent by you together with the product. In this case Datatrans will provide additional data for printing an ESR slip. This feature must be active with the processor as well as Datatrans. You must then process this data yourself. Only supported by Powerpay. Otherwise Powerpay will send the invoice in your stead.
column2: Here you can set if the invoice will be sent by you together with the product. In this case Datatrans will provide additional data for printing an ESR slip. This feature must be active with the processor as well as Datatrans. You must then process this data yourself. Only supported by Powerpay. Otherwise Powerpay will send the invoice in your stead.

column1: Here you can specify the text, which is shown to the customer on the Easypay website. If the text contains the tag {id}, it will be replaced with the order number.
column2: Here you can specify the text, which is shown to the customer on the Easypay website. If the text contains the tag {id}, it will be replaced with the order number.

column1: If a product is in stock only once and the payment of the customer ordering this product fails or is aborted, it won't be available until the order is canceled (see timeout option below). Enable this setting to cancel the customer's pending orders when he returns to the cart page and a product is not available anymore.
column2: Si sólo hay una unidad en stock y el pago del cliente (comprando esta unidad) falla, el producto está reservado hasta que la orden esta cancelada (vea la opción de tiempo de espera). Activa esta opción si desea que el producto NO está reservado. Ordenes con un estado de pago fallido o annulado entonces serán canceladas inmediatamente.

column1: If a product is in stock only once and the payment of the customer ordering this product fails or is aborted, it won't be available until the order is canceled (see timeout option below). Enable this setting to cancel the customer's pending orders when he returns to the cart page and a product is not available anymore. Be careful though: If you enable this option, there is a chance that payments are made with the corresponding order being already canceled.
column2: If a product is in stock only once and the payment of the customer ordering this product fails or is aborted, it won't be available until the order is canceled (see timeout option below). Enable this setting to cancel the customer's pending orders when he returns to the cart page and a product is not available anymore. Be careful though: If you enable this option, there is a chance that payments are made with the corresponding order being already canceled.

column1: When the store is not available (network outage, server failure or any other outage), when the feedback of Datatrans is sent, then the transaction state is not updated. Hence no order confirmation e-mail is sent and the order is not in the paid state. By activating the transaction update, such transactions can be authorized later over direct link. To use this feature the update service must be activated and the API username and the API password must be set.
column2: When the store is not available (network outage, server failure or any other outage), when the feedback of Datatrans is sent, then the transaction state is not updated. Hence no order confirmation e-mail is sent and the order is not in the paid state. By activating the transaction update, such transactions can be authorized later over direct link. To use this feature the update service must be activated and the API username and the API password must be set.

column1: When the store is not available (network outage, server failure or any other outage), when the feedback of Datatrans is sent, then the transaction state is not updated. Hence no order confirmation e-mail is sent and the order is not in the paid state. By activating the transaction update, such transactions can be authorized.
column2: Cuando la tienda no está disponible (interrupción de la red, falla en el servidor o cualquier otra interrupción), cuando se envía el votaciones de Datatrans, entonces el estado de la transacción no se actualiza. De ahí que no se envía ninguna confirmación del pedido por e-mail y la orden no se encuentra en estado de pago. Mediante la activación de la actualización de la transacción, tales operaciones pueden ser autorizadas.
